# Frontend Standards (Global Rules for This Project)

Please follow these rules for ALL code created or modified in this repository:

1. Always refer to FRONTEND_STANDARDS.md for coding conventions.
2. Use TypeScript for all files.
3. Use the predefined folder structure:
   src/components/, src/pages/, src/hooks/, src/types/
4. All components must:
   - Use PascalCase
   - Have a Props interface named <ComponentName>Props
   - Be accessible (aria labels, roles, described-by)
5. All forms must:
   - Use React Hook Form
   - Use reusable components like TextField, SelectField, CheckboxGroup
6. All validation schemas must be Zod-based and placed in /types or /schemas.

If any code request conflicts with these rules,
ALWAYS choose the version that aligns with FRONTEND_STANDARDS.md.
